# Project Rules

- Minimize dependencies. Prefer vanilla JS/CSS/HTML over adding libraries. Every dependency must justify its weight.
- The build output (`dist/`) must be a self-contained static site that works on any web server with zero configuration.
- Keep the project handoff-friendly: engineers receiving the built files should never need Node.js, npm, or any build tools.
